  "body": "Please see the file [NEWS](https://github.com/upx/upx/blob/master/NEWS) for a detailed list of changes.\r\n\r\nNote: all versions are functionally equivalent, i.e. each version can handle **all** executable formats, so you only need the file that runs on your host OS.\r\n\r\nSecurity/VirusTotal links are listed in the pinned issue https://github.com/upx/upx/issues/437\r\n\r\n| Asset / File | Description / Host OS |\r\n| --- | --- |\r\n| [upx-5.1.1-amd64_linux.tar.xz](https://github.com/upx/upx/releases/download/v5.1.1/upx-5.1.1-amd64_linux.tar.xz) | UPX - Linux version, statically linked |\r\n| upx-5.1.1-arm64_linux.tar.xz | UPX - Linux version, statically linked |\r\n| upx-5.1.1-armeb_linux.tar.xz | UPX - Linux version, statically linked |\r\n| upx-5.1.1-arm_linux.tar.xz | UPX - Linux version, statically linked |\r\n| upx-5.1.1-dos.zip | UPX - DOS version |\r\n| upx-5.1.1-i386_linux.tar.xz | UPX - Linux version, statically linked |\r\n| upx-5.1.1-mipsel_linux.tar.xz | UPX - Linux version, statically linked |\r\n| upx-5.1.1-mips_linux.tar.xz | UPX - Linux version, statically linked |\r\n| upx-5.1.1-powerpc64le_linux.tar.xz | UPX - Linux version, statically linked |\r\n| upx-5.1.1-powerpc_linux.tar.xz | UPX - Linux version, statically linked |\r\n| upx-5.1.1-riscv64_linux.tar.xz | UPX - Linux version, statically linked |\r\n| [upx-5.1.1-src.tar.xz](https://github.com/upx/upx/releases/download/v5.1.1/upx-5.1.1-src.tar.xz) | UPX - **source code tarball** |\r\n| upx-5.1.1-win32.zip | UPX - X86 Win32 version |\r\n| [upx-5.1.1-win64.zip](https://github.com/upx/upx/releases/download/v5.1.1/upx-5.1.1-win64.zip)  | UPX - X64 Win64 version |\r\n",
